<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFF8F6168CB33F3FF79AF39E" pageId="60" pageNumber="118" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFF8F6168CB33F3FF79AF39E" blockId="60.[1450,2661,2136,3156]" pageId="60" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFF8F6168CB33F3FF8B5F4DB" bold="true" box="[1453,1808,2851,2880]" pageId="60" pageNumber="118">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List (as N. 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFF8F61683073F3FFA7DF4FC" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1906" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Cynopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutus">minutus</taxonomicName>
). The Lesser Tube-nosed Fruit Bat might be threatened by mining and logging that occurs throughout its distribution. It occurs in Manusela National Park (Seram Island). Virtually nothing is known about its ecology, and there is considerable confusion about its taxonomy. Additional research is needed, including sampling efforts because it is known from only a few specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
